# Bench Recall Quality

## Question

Add a consumption leg to brainbench: known-answer retrieval queries over
the distilled layer ("what did we decide about X" with a canonical page as
truth), scored for hit-rank across the three pull surfaces (sessions
search, qmd hybrid, paper index). Benchmark prompts live OUTSIDE indexed
Brain roots (qmd spike caveat). Baseline now, rerun as the corpus grows —
recall quality measured, not vibed. Page-quality benching stays on the
observational-memory map.

## Resolution

Shipped the Brainbench consumption leg beside the existing edition and graph
legs in `joelclaw-wiki`. Five held-out known-answer prompts live at
`fixtures/brainbench/recall-quality-v1.json`, outside indexed Brain roots.
The runner scores canonical-page hit rank, Recall@1/3/5, MRR, latency, and
adapter errors for `sessions-search`, qmd hybrid, and the paper's
`brain_graph_nodes` index; it appends to the existing score log and writes a
per-run JSON receipt.

July baseline: sessions-search **1/5, MRR 0.20**; qmd hybrid **3/5, MRR
0.34**; paper index **0/5, MRR 0.00**. The paper zero exposed real stale and
privacy-gated index coverage rather than a runtime failure. Full receipt:
[Recall quality baseline — July 2026](../../resources/recall-quality-baseline-2026-07.svx).

## Resolution (2026-07-13)

Baseline landed: [recall-quality-baseline-2026-07](../../resources/recall-quality-baseline-2026-07.svx) — known-answer fixtures outside indexed roots, scored across sessions-search, qmd hybrid, and paper index; reviewer PASS. Rerun as the corpus grows.
